INSTALL
=======

To the fans of vim, you can use the .vim files to write lpmd control file using colors. It is the first version available.

1. First step, set the filetypes. 

You will need also create the file 'filetype.vim' in the folder 

~/.vim/

folder, and write these lines:

" The lpmd plugcode format
au BufRead,BufNewFile *.plugcode setfiletype lpplugcode
au BufRead,BufNewFile *.control setfiletype lpcontrol
au BufRead,BufNewFile *.lpplugin setfiletype lpplugin


2.- Install the files.

To use this, copy the *.vim file to your personal syntax styles directory:

cp *.vim ~/.vim/syntax/

If you don't have the previous folder, you can create it.

lpcontrol.vim : Edit control files with colors in vim.
lplugcode.vim : Edit plugcode files with colors in vim.
lpplugin.vim  : Additional content of plugins, not used externally.

3.- Enjoy

Now you can use the vim to edit .control and .plugcode files with color enhancements.
